\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 70. D. langeanus }Willk. in Willk. & Lange,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Hisp.}{\b  3}: 690 (1878) ({\i D. gredensis} Pau ex Caball.). Laxly caespitose perennial, often with rather slender, trailing stems; stems 10-20 cm, slender, simple or little-branched. Leaves 1-2 cm, rather thick and rigid, acute, canaliculate when dry; cauline leaves 2-4 pairs, shorter than internodes, erect. Epicalyx-scales 4, c. ¼ as long as calyx, ovate, subacute, shortly apiculate or obtuse, the inner wider than the outer. Calyx 8-10 × 2 mm, almost cylindrical. Petal-limb 5-7 mm, dentate to entire, pink, glabrous. •{\i  N.W. & W.C. Spain.} Hs ?Lu.
